  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Beautician",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities and Duties</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Skincare:</strong> Perform facials, analyze skin types, and suggest treatments or products.</li><li><strong>Hair Care:</strong> Cut, style, color, shampoo, and treat hair.</li><li><strong>Nail Care:</strong> Provide manicures, pedicures, and nail art.</li><li><strong>Hair Removal:</strong> Perform waxing, sugaring, or electrolysis.</li><li><strong>Makeup:</strong> Apply makeup for daily wear or special events.</li><li><strong>Client Relations & Sales:</strong> Greet clients, understand their needs, offer expert advice, and cross-sell salon products and services.</li><li><strong>Hygiene & Safety:</strong> Clean and sterilize tools and workstations, adhering to salon sanitation standards.</li><li><strong>Administrative:</strong> Manage appointments, handle payments, and maintain client records. </li></ul><p><strong>Requirements and Skills</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Certification/Licensing:</strong> Valid state or national licensure as a cosmetologist, beautician, or aesthetician.</li><li><strong>Industry Knowledge:</strong> Familiarity with modern beauty techniques, trends, and product lines.</li><li><strong>Customer Service:</strong> Friendly, professional demeanor with excellent communication skills.</li><li><strong>Physical Stamina:</strong> Ability to stand for long periods and work with hands. </li></ul>",
